# Cursor Hooks

Hooks run custom scripts before or after agent actions. Configured in `.cursor/hooks.json` (project root).

Reference: [Cursor Hooks Docs](https://cursor.com/docs/agent/hooks)

## Hook events

| Event | When | Use case |
| ----- | ---- | -------- |
| `afterFileEdit` | After agent edits a file | Auto-format, lint, validate |
| `beforeShellExecution` | Before shell command runs | Block dangerous commands |
| `afterShellExecution` | After shell command completes | Audit logs, capture PR URLs |
| `stop` | Agent session ends | Final verification, cleanup |
| `sessionStart` | New conversation begins | Inject context, set env vars |
| `preToolUse` | Before any tool runs | Validate tool usage (with matcher) |
| `beforeReadFile` | Before agent reads a file | Redact secrets, access control |

## Current project hooks

### afterFileEdit

- **Lint** (`after-edit-lint.sh`, 15s timeout): Prettier + ESLint `--fix` in a single script
- **console.log** (`after-edit-console-warn.sh`, 5s timeout): warns if `console.log` found in edited file

### preToolUse

- **Fallback review** (prompt hook, 12s timeout): Cursor reviews pending edit operations for silent fallbacks before applying them. This is the closest Cursor-native adaptation of [claude-pre-commit.sh](https://gist.github.com/boxabirds/9e9261700533c7636c940e2a107c27b5): same intent, but enforced on agent file edits (`Write`, `ApplyPatch`, `EditNotebook`) instead of a Git hook. It is LLM-evaluated and conservative by design.

### beforeShellExecution (with matcher)

- **Guard**: blocks `rm -rf /`, force push to main/master, asks before `--no-verify`

### afterShellExecution

- **PR logger** (5s timeout): captures PR URL and review command after `gh pr create`

### stop

- **console.log audit** (10s timeout): checks all git-modified JS/TS files for `console.log`

## Git pre-commit vs Cursor hooks

Cursor **does not expose a native Git pre-commit event** for its model hooks. Prompt hooks run inside the agent/tool lifecycle, not inside Husky or Git itself.

- If the goal is **Cursor-native model review**, `preToolUse` is the right place.
- If the goal is **true Git pre-commit review for every commit**, that requires an external CLI or API call from Husky. Cursor's built-in prompt hooks cannot be called from `.husky/pre-commit`.

## Real Git pre-commit

This repo also uses a real Git hook:

- **Versioned hook**: `.githooks/pre-commit`
- **Local activator**: `.git/hooks/pre-commit` delegates to the versioned script without editing `core.hooksPath`
- **Checks**: `.cursor/scripts/pre-commit-checks.mjs`

Current deterministic checks:

- Parse staged `.json` files to fail fast on invalid JSON
- Run `sh -n` on staged `.sh` files when `sh` is available
- If `.cursor/hooks.json` or files under `.cursor/hooks/` are staged, verify that `hooks.json` only references existing hook scripts

